SIMPLE: slink
RECORDS: 4

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Slink
<hw>Slink</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.</pos>
<conjf>Slunk</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>, <mark>Archaic</mark>
<conjf>Slank</conjf> <pr>(<?/)</pr>; <pos>p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Slunk</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Slinking</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[AS. <ets>slincan</ets>;
probably akin to G. <ets>schleichen</ets>, E. <ets>sleek</ets>. See
<er>Sleek</er>, <pos>a.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To creep away
meanly; to steal away; to sneak.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧To <xex>slink</xex> away
and hide.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Tale of Beryn.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Back to the thicket <qex>slunk</qex>⟦br⟧
The guilty serpent.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>There were some few who <qex>slank</qex> obliquely from them as
they passed.</q> <rj><qau>Landor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To miscarry; -- said of female beasts.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Slink</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Slink
<hw>Slink</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To cast prematurely; -- said of
female beasts; <as>as, a cow that <ex>slinks</ex> her
calf</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Slink</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Slink
<hw>Slink</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Produced prematurely;
<as>as, a <ex>slink</ex> calf</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Thin; lean.</def> <mark>[Scot.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Slink</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Slink
<hw>Slink</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The young of a beast
brought forth prematurely, esp. a calf brought forth before its
time.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A thievish fellow; a sneak.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng.
& Scot.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Slinky</ent>⟦br⟧
